<p>The objective is to override <code>ggplot()</code> alphabitcal ordering of factor/character levels on the x-axis.</p>  <p>The example: </p>  <pre><code>df &lt;- data.frame(       type=c("boat","car","yacht","train","horse","bike"),freq=c(60,20,11,10,5,2))  ggplot(df, aes(x=type, y=freq))+geom_bar(stat='identity',fill="blue")  </code></pre>  <p>The desired effect: boat > car > yacht ... plotted in this order from leftest to rightest side.</p>  <p>Tried solutions from previous Stack <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/12774210/how-do-you-specifically-order-ggplot2-x-axis-instead-of-alphabetical-order">Q1</a> and <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/3253641/how-to-change-the-order-of-a-discrete-x-scale-in-ggplot">Q2</a> (eg. reoder) to no avail.  Any thoughts? Thanks guys.</p>